data.chText: 重要事件；重要阶段；转折点；里程碑
data.enText: a very important stage or event in the development of sth
a stone by the side of a road that shows how far it is to the next town and to other places

tr: stone post at side of a road to show distances
a significant event in your life (or in a project)

value.def: A milestone is an important event in the history or development of something or someone.

example.ex: He said the launch of the party represented a milestone in Zambian history...
example.tran: 他说该党的创立是赞比亚历史上的一个里程碑。

example.ex: Starting school is a milestone for both children and parents.
example.tran: 对于孩子和家长而言，开始上学是一件大事。

value.tran: 里程碑;重大事件;重要阶段

value.def: A milestone is a stone by the side of a road showing the distances to particular places.
value.tran: （路边显示到某地距离的）里程碑，里程标志
